From f0f4fc4a3bcd3f66072971234de40b81b6ebd9ff Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Micheal Waltz <micheal@ecliptik.com>
Date: Sat, 25 Apr 2026 20:13:23 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 37/37] diag: env-gated DOSKUTSU_NO_AUDIO bypass for
 SoundManager::init
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Phase 8 real-HW diagnostic. SoundManager::init() ultimately reaches
SDL3-DOS's Sound Blaster DSP probe via MIX_CreateMixerDevice ->
SDL_OpenAudioDevice. PR #15377's SDL3-DOS audio backend has no
real-hardware test coverage, and on a real Vibra16S CT2490 (g2k
machine, 2026-04-25 attempt) the probe wedges with no further log
output past Renderer::showLoadingScreen().

Setting DOSKUTSU_NO_AUDIO=1 in the DOS environment skips the init
call entirely. If the engine reaches the title screen with this set,
audio init is confirmed as the wall and the SB DSP probe in SDL3-DOS
needs a real fix (most likely a bounded-timeout wrapper around the
DSP version-query loop). If the engine still hangs, audio is ruled
out and we look elsewhere (font load, NPC table, script init, etc).

Not for shipping. Leaving the env var set in production = no audio.
This is intentionally an env-var bypass rather than a build-time
flag so the same DOSKUTSU.EXE artifact serves both the audio-on
"normal" run and the audio-off "diagnostic" run — one tarball, two
boots.
---
 src/main.cpp | 16 +++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/main.cpp b/src/main.cpp
index 1bafafa..76a31f6 100644
--- a/src/main.cpp
+++ b/src/main.cpp
@@ -374,7 +374,21 @@ int main(int argc, char *argv[])
 
   Renderer::getInstance()->showLoadingScreen();
 
-  if (!SoundManager::getInstance()->init())
+  // DOS-PORT: env-gated audio-init bypass for Phase 8 real-HW diagnostics.
+  // SoundManager::init() ultimately calls into SDL3-DOS's Sound Blaster DSP
+  // probe (via MIX_CreateMixerDevice -> SDL_OpenAudioDevice). PR #15377's
+  // SDL3-DOS audio backend has no real-hardware test coverage; on a real
+  // Vibra16S (g2k machine) this path wedges with no log output past
+  // showLoadingScreen(). Setting DOSKUTSU_NO_AUDIO=1 in the DOS environment
+  // skips audio init so we can localize the hang. If the engine reaches the
+  // title screen with this set, audio init is confirmed as the wall and the
+  // SB DSP probe needs a real fix. Not for shipping — leaving this in place
+  // means no audio.
+  if (std::getenv("DOSKUTSU_NO_AUDIO"))
+  {
+    LOG_INFO("DOSKUTSU_NO_AUDIO set; bypassing SoundManager::init() for diagnostics");
+  }
+  else if (!SoundManager::getInstance()->init())
   {
     fatal("Failed to initialize sound.");
     return 1;
